<div id="News" class="tabcontent"><center><br>
  <h1>Tapa Making Guide!</h1>
  <hr style="height:5px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">
 <h2> How to Marinate and Cook Tapa</h2>
   <ul>
   <h3>Ingredients needed</h3>
  <li>1kg beef</li>
  <li>½ cup + 2 tbsps. soy sauce</li>
  <li>½ tsp. salt</li>
  <li>1 tsp. black pepper</li>
  <li>½ - 1 tbsp. sugar </li>
  <li>2 pcs. whole heads of garlic with skin </li>
  <li>1 tbsp. calamansi juice</li>
  <li>½ tsp. baking soda</li>
  <li>½ cup cola or apple juice</li><br>
  <hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">
  <h3> Materials Needed</h3>
   <li> A Non-stick Pan </li>
    <li>Spatula </li>
     <li>Measuring cups and spoons</li>
      <li>Bowl </li>
      <li>Tongs</li>
      <li>Utensils</li>
      <li>Chopping board</li><br></ul>
      <hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">
      <ol><hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18"> <h3>Marination process
       </h3>
    <li>Prepare the meat </li>
  <li>Mix the soy sauce, black pepper, sugar, garlic, calamansi juice, baking soda, juice/cola in a blender to make the marinade.</li>
   <li>Then mix the meat and marinade together</li>
    <li>Seal it and keep it in the refrigerator for a week to marinate</li><br><hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18"> <h3>Watch this video to get a better idea!</h3> <iframe width="380" height="280" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qDO1P-sIMPM" title="TAPA MARINATING GROUP 4" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe><br><br><hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">
<h3> Was this Recipe Helpful?</h3> <p3> Press "OK" for Yes! Press "Cancel" for No!</p3><br><br>
<button onclick="myFunction()">Press Me!</button>

<p id="demo"></p>
