  }
  document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = txt;
}
</script></ol> <ol>
 <hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">  <h3> Cooking Process</h3>
  <li>After leaving it for one week, defrost your meat for 30 minutes and then open your meat from the bag, or after marinating it.</li>
  <li>Heat up the pan with 8 tbsp of water, and then after the water is dried up in the pan, proceed to add a little bit of oil and cook it until it is brown.
</li>
   <li>After cooking, Cut the beef tapa into bite size pieces, after that you may plate it with garlic fried rice (or just normal white rice) topped with sliced green onions and with egg and cucumber on the side (optional).</li><br> <hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18"><h3>Watch this video to get a better idea!</h3><iframe width="380" height="280" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/I00vAbnpGQg" title="TAPA COOKING GROUP 4" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe><br><br><hr style="height:3px;border-width:0;color:gray;background-color:#9A3A18">
